(7612,7612,1, 'II Conferencia Electrónica sobre Usos Sostenibles y Conservación del Ecosistema Páramo en los Andes: "Los Páramos como fuente de Agua, Mitos, Realidades, Retos y Acciones"', 'Este documento contiene la síntesis de la II Conferencia Electrónica sobre usos sostenibles y conservación del Ecosistema Páramo Andino, el cual se enfoca en la potencialidad de aprovechar económicamente los servicios ambientales que brindan los páramosy cuya sostenibilidad depende de que se mantengan íntegras sus funciones ecológicas.', 'Este documento contiene la síntesis de la II Conferencia Electrónica sobre usos sostenibles y conservación del Ecosistema Páramo Andino, el cual se enfoca en la potencialidad de aprovechar económicamente los servicios ambientales que brindan los páramosy cuya sostenibilidad depende de que se mantengan íntegras sus funciones ecológicas.', '', 958453200, 2),
(14654,14654,1, 'Mountains Ecosystems. Advantages that contribute to their development', 'Mountains ecosystems and its biodiversity are the principal topics of this paper. Based on this, the authors wonder about the development possibilities in Andes Mountains, showing its principal features and the factors that affect them.', 'Mountains ecosystems and its biodiversity are the principal topics of this paper. Based on this, the authors wonder about the development possibilities in Andes Mountains, showing its principal features and the factors that affect them.', '', 957243600, 2),
(7549,7549,1, 'Integrating Remote Sensing, GIS, and Modeling for Land-Use Monitoring in the Arid/Semi-Arid Andes (DME-Sur): FINAL PROGRAM REPORT', 'This report summarizes the activities and outputs of the project Integrating Remote Sensing (RS), Geographic Information Systems (GIS), and Modeling for Land Use Monitoring in the Arid/Semi-arid Andes (DME-Sur). The activities reported were mainly financed by the Ecoregional Fund to Support Methodological Initiatives and conducted as an approved activity of the Consortium for the Sustainable Development of the Andes (CONDESAN). The goal of the project was to develop and test methodologies to improve the predictive performance of crop, pasture, and animal production models through the inclusion of remotely sensed qualitative and quantitative data. The research were conducted in Peru (Puno) and Bolivia.', 'This report summarizes the activities and outputs of the project Integrating Remote Sensing (RS), Geographic Information Systems (GIS), and Modeling for Land Use Monitoring in the Arid/Semi-arid Andes (DME-Sur). The activities reported were mainly financed by the Ecoregional Fund to Support Methodological Initiatives and conducted as an approved activity of the Consortium for the Sustainable Development of the Andes (CONDESAN). The goal of the project was to develop and test methodologies to improve the predictive performance of crop, pasture, and animal production models through the inclusion of remotely sensed qualitative and quantitative data. The research were conducted in Peru (Puno) and Bolivia.', '', 957070800, 2),
